<TITLE> Bangladesh business confidence improving: survey </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 13 (bdnews24.com)  Business confidence is improving, according to a just published survey carried out in the last quarter of 2009. Overall business confidence, on a scale of 1-100 in three areasinvestment, employment and profitabilityrose to 56 from 51 in the previous quarter, the survey said. The improvement was in line with what was expected, said a report by the surveyors. Investments are expected to increase significantly in the first four months of the current year with an accompanying rise in employment, the report says. The business confidence survey is carried out by Bangladesh Investment Climate Fund (BICF), managed by IFC, a World Bank body, on a regular basis. For the latest survey, some 1440 businesses were surveyed round the country over the last quarter (Oct-Dec) of 2009. Around 700 businesses were surveyed in the previous quarter. The findings were presented at a meeting jointly organised by BICF and International Chamber of Commerce-Bangladesh (ICC-B) at the Dhaka Chamber of Commerce and Industries (DCCI) on Saturday.
